  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Multimedia Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>We’re looking for a <strong>Multimedia Designer</strong> who is both visually creative and technically curious. You’ll be involved in the <strong>conception, design, and execution of multimedia assets</strong> across digital campaigns, graphics projects, and launch initiatives. This role is ideal for someone who enjoys designing, animating, and experimenting with interactive or coded elements to bring ideas to life.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conceptualise and create <strong>digital creative assets</strong> for multimedia projects and campaign launches</li><li>Design visually compelling <strong>graphics, layouts, and visual systems</strong> across various digital platforms</li><li>Produce <strong>motion graphics and animations</strong> for videos, social content, presentations, and digital experiences</li><li>Support interactive or digital executions using <strong>basic coding (HTML) or scripting knowledge</strong> where required</li><li>Collaborate closely with creative, content, and project teams to deliver ideas from concept to execution</li><li>Ensure all work aligns with brand guidelines, creative direction, and project objectives</li><li>Stay updated on design, animation, and technology trends to continuously improve creative output</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Strong understanding of <strong>creative design principles</strong>, layout, typography, and visual storytelling</li><li>Proficient in <strong>Adobe Creative Suite</strong> (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign) and related design tools</li><li>Proficient in <strong>animation and video software</strong>, including Adobe Animate, After Effects, and Premiere Pro</li><li>Working knowledge of <strong>coding or interactive technologies</strong> (e.g. HTML, CSS, JavaScript, or similar) required</li><li>Minimum <strong>2 years of agency experience</strong> preferred; <strong>fresh graduates with strong portfolios are welcome to apply</strong></li><li>Ability to manage multiple projects and meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment</li></ul><p><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul><li>A <strong>team player</strong> who is open-minded and collaborative</li><li>Curious, adaptable, and always keen to explore <strong>new and better ways of doing things</strong></li><li>Passionate about design, motion, and digital experiences</li><li>Motivated to grow and contribute to a <strong>dynamic and expanding team</strong></li></ul>",
